🔄 What is a Watchdog?
A watchdog is like a safety supervisor for your firmware.
Your code must periodically report: “I’m alive.”
If it fails to do so → the watchdog automatically resets the system.

⚠️ What happens when firmware hangs?
Your entire system becomes useless — especially in real-time applications like IoT monitoring, automation, or industrial control

🔥 Key Insight:
A system without a watchdog is a system waiting to fail silently.
